{
  "texts": [
    "H-IT performs better with balanced accuracy and NLL.",
    "The AUROC and NLL need to be interpreted in context: Weasel 2.0, RDST and MR-Hydra use classifiers that only produce 0/1 predictions.",
    "This means they will inevitably perform poorly on AUROC and NLL.",
    "For context, Figure 40 shows the scatter plot of HC2 against the next best (MR-Hydra) and the worst performing (PF).",
    "It is worth reiterating that PF is significantly better than both EE and 1-NN DTW, both of which were considered state of the art until recently."
  ]
}